        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-10-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-10-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="329" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <head>[Telegram.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Liverpool,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-10-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 12—3 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Screw steamer Laurel, 269 tons, one funnel, two masts, sailed from Liverpool on
                    Sunday, with Captain Semmes, a number of guns, ten officers, and one hundred
                    men, supposed for some other vessel. Advise consuls at Madeira, &amp;c., and
                    naval officers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CONSUL LIVERPOOL.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Minister</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Lisbon.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
